node.text: I cooked up my delicious “Ginger-Miso Pasta Salad” with my friends over at @todayshow to show them how easy and refreshing this recipe is! 💕 With a few Persian cucumbers, bell peppers, edamame, broccoli, and toasted sesame seeds, you’re gonna love adding this summer salad to your menu because it packs easily and can be served at any temperature! ☀️ Recipe link in IG stories! 😘

#compassion

🥶 It’s been chilly out, so let’s cook my yummy “Greek Lemon Chicken Soup” to warm you and the family up! 🥰 This recipe is so Deeelicious! 💫 
•
INGREDIENTS✨
Deselect All
4 cups chicken stock
1 small carrot, halved 
1 stalk celery, halved 
1 sprig dill, plus sprigs for garnish
1 shallot, halved
Kosher salt 
1 boneless, skinless chicken breast (about 6 ounces) 
1/3 rounded cup orzo 
2 large eggs 
3 tablespoons fresh lemon juice
________
DIRECTIONS✨
1. In a large saucepan, combine the chicken stock with 4 cups water, the carrot, celery, dill, shallot and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken breast, lower the heat to a bare simmer, and cook, turning occasionally, until just cooked through, 12 to 15 minutes. Transfer the breast to a plate. Remove the carrot, celery, dill and shallot from the broth, and discard.
•
2. Raise the heat to a brisk simmer. Add the orzo to the broth and simmer until tender, 6 to 8 minutes. Meanwhile, shred the chicken.
•
3. Whisk the eggs with the lemon juice in a medium bowl. When the orzo is cooked, slowly ladle about 1/2 cup of the hot broth into the egg mixture while whisking constantly. Pour back into the saucepan and cook, whisking occasionally, just until the broth returns to a simmer, about 2 minutes. Turn off the heat, add the shredded chicken, and season with salt.
•
4.Ladle the soup into bowls and garnish with dill.

node.text: 👩🏻‍🍳 This Sunday on #ValeriesHomeCooking, I’m testing the boundaries of what a cookie can be! 🍪 I’m making cookies that are good for any time of day, starting with Breakfast Sandwich Cookies. Yes, I said breakfast sandwich cookies! 😋 I also bake Chocolate and Orange Hazelnut Cookies, Coconut Chocolate Chip Cookies, and Thyme and Gruyere Savory Cookies, and I’m rollin’ up Almond Butter, Oat, Cranberry Cookie Dough Balls, too. 💕 Get your sweet tooth tuned into @foodnetwork this Sunday at 1130am! 😚 Have a great weekend! ☺️

node.text: 👩🏻‍🍳 This Sunday I’m showing my beautiful friend @hodakotb an excellent summer meal she can make for her family, and I’m letting you in on a secret 🤫 my girl can cook!! 💕 We’re sharing tips for getting through the day with grace and gratitude! 🙏🏼 We start with a fresh Arugula Salad with Quick Pickled Grapes, Fennel, Pear and Brie and then make a juicy Flank Steak with Lemon Lime Herb Sauce, Smoky Tomato Eggplant Dip with Grilled Sourdough and Citrus Grape Smash Cocktails to set the mood! 🎉 Sunday on @foodnetwork 1130 AM!!
